{
  "info": {
    "name": "PyPNM API",
    "description": "**Proactive Network Maintenance (PNM) API for DOCSIS devices**\n\nPython-based RESTful API for accessing, analyzing, and visualizing DOCSIS 3.1/4.0 PNM telemetry.\n\n**PyPNM provides structured endpoints for:**\n- Downstream and upstream OFDM/OFDMA diagnostics\n- OFDM RxMER and Channel Estimation Analysis\n- Modulation profile decoding and traffic stats\n- FEC summary and profile-specific correction metrics\n- Spectrum capture, constellation display, and pre-equalization\n- TFTP/SNMP-based file retrieval and modem polling\n\nDesigned for integration into dashboards, automation pipelines, and engineering tools to assist with plant health monitoring, anomaly detection, and DOCSIS signal quality evaluation.\n\n\ud83d\udd17 [**GitHub - PyPNM**](https://github.com/mgarcia01752/PyPNM)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "45031353-a1b2-4c3d-8e4f-5f6a7b8c9d0e"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Collection-level test utilities and common validations",
          "",
          "// Validate response time is reasonable (under 30 seconds for PNM operations)",
          "pm.test('Response time is acceptable', function() {",
          "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(30000);",
          "});",
          "",
          "// Check for common error patterns",
          "if (pm.response.code >= 400) {",
          "    pm.test('Error response has proper structure', function() {",
          "        const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
          "        pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('detail').or.to.have.property('error').or.to.have.property('message');",
          "    });",
          "}",
          "",
          "// Utility function to validate MAC address format",
          "pm.globals.set('validateMacAddress', function(mac) {",
          "    const macRegex = /^([0-9A-Fa-f]{2}[:-]){5}([0-9A-Fa-f]{2})$/;",
          "    return macRegex.test(mac);",
          "});",
          "",
          "// Utility function to validate IP address format",
          "pm.globals.set('validateIpAddress', function(ip) {",
          "    const ipRegex = /^(?:(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9][0-9]?)\\.){3}(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9][0-9]?)$/;",
          "    return ipRegex.test(ip);",
          "});",
          "",
          "// Utility function to validate transaction ID format",
          "pm.globals.set('validateTransactionId', function(txnId) {",
          "    return typeof txnId === 'string' && txnId.length > 0;",
          "});",
          "",
          "// Check if response has valid JSON content type",
          "if (pm.response.code < 300) {",
          "    const contentType = pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type');",
          "    if (contentType && contentType.includes('application/json')) {",
          "        pm.test('Response has valid JSON content type', function() {",
          "            pm.expect(contentType).to.include('application/json');",
          "        });",
          "    }",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "System",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get System Description",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"cable_modem\": {\n    \"mac_address\": \"38:AD:2B:3E:86:54\",\n    \"ip_address\": \"172.19.32.241\",\n    \"snmp\": {\n      \"snmp_v2c\": {\n        \"community\": \"public\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/system/sysDescr",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "system",
                "sysDescr"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Fetches the system description from a DOCSIS modem. This endpoint performs an SNMP query to fetch the system description (`sysDescr`) string from a DOCSIS modem, then parses it to extract hardware, software, bootloader, vendor, and model details."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains system description data', function() {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.be.an('object');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get System Uptime",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"cable_modem\": {\n    \"mac_address\": \"38:AD:2B:3E:86:54\",\n    \"ip_address\": \"172.19.32.241\",\n    \"snmp\": {\n      \"snmp_v2c\": {\n        \"community\": \"public\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/system/upTime",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "system",
                "upTime"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Retrieves the SNMP system uptime from a DOCSIS cable modem, expressed as a human-readable duration. Useful for identifying recent reboots or uptime trends."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains uptime data', function() {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.be.an('object');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "description": "System-level SNMP endpoints for DOCSIS devices",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// System folder tests - validate SNMP connectivity",
              "pm.test('SNMP response received', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 400, 401, 404, 500]);",
